13/08/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Prime Minister Simeon Saxe-Coburg, Chief Prosecutor Nikola Filchev and Interior Ministry Chief Secretary Boyko Borissov met on Thursday (12 August) to discuss legal measures to combat organised crime. 
Filchev and Borissov urged the government to tighten measures for detaining known criminals and introduce stiffer penalties. 
They also lobbied for extra law enforcement funding and better co-ordination between the judiciary and the chief prosecutor's office. 
(Mediapool, BNT - 12/08/04)
